org.jetel.hadoop.service.mapreduce

Class HadoopCounterGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<HadoopCounterKey>
      • org.jetel.hadoop.service.mapreduce.HadoopCounterGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<HadoopCounterKey>, java.util.Collection<HadoopCounterKey>

    public class HadoopCounterGroup
extends java.util.AbstractCollection<HadoopCounterKey>

    Represents named and ordered collection of HadoopCounterKey instances. It corresponds to Hadoop API specific counters group that consists of all counters that are identified by Enum constants of the same enumeration. This class provides abstraction from this Hadoop API specific enumerations.

    Instances of this class are immutable. Equality relation is defined on instances of this class by overriding methods Object.hashCode() and Object.equals(Object). Two instances are equal if and only if they have equal group name.

    Since:
    rel-3-4-0-M2

    • Constructor Detail

      • HadoopCounterGroup

        public HadoopCounterGroup(java.util.Collection<HadoopCounterKey> counters,
                  java.lang.String groupName,
                  java.lang.String groupDisplayName)
        Initializes new counter group using given list of counters, group name and group display name.
        Parameters:
        counters - Non-null nor empty collection of counters that new counters group will include. By contract, all the counters keys in this collection must have their counterGroupName attribute set to string equal to name of this group.
        groupName - Unique, non-null group name for this group. By contract, this must be string equal to class name of corresponding Hadoop API specific counters enumeration that is represented by constructed instance.
        groupDisplayName - Display name of the counters group intended to be displayed to user or null.
        See Also:
        HadoopCounterKey.getGroupName()

      • HadoopCounterGroup

        public HadoopCounterGroup(T[] hadoopApiCounterKeys,
                  java.lang.String groupDisplayName,
                  HadoopCounterDisplayNameGetter<T> countersDisplayNameGetter)
        Automatically creates HadoopCounterKey instances for enum constants representing individual counters and initializes new counter group with them. A name of the Enum class is used as both group name and group name of created counters.
        Parameters:
        hadoopApiCounterKeys - Non-null nor empty array of enum constants that represents Hadoop API counters keys that are to be used to create HadoopCounterKeys of this group.
        groupDisplayName - Display name of the counters group intended to be displayed to user.
        countersDisplayNameGetter - Is used to initialize display names of individual HadoopCounterKeys when creating them. When null, display names are not created.
